OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCFreeview switch-off: a history
OL,4,Clesson
OL,5,
OL,6,FIn practice, the only big overnight
OL,7,Fchange in 1971 concerned any price, or
OL,8,Ffraction of a price, of less than 2.5p
OL,9,F` old sixpences (value 2.5p) remained
OL,10,Flegal tender until 1980.
OL,12,FThere was advice on how to use up old
OL,13,Fcopper coins in the weeks afterwards.
OL,14,FOverpay and get your change in decimal
OL,15,Fcurrency.
OL,17,FAnd yet, this change was still a
OL,18,Fworrying and anxious time for a
OL,19,Fminority. Great efforts were made to
OL,20,Ftry to make it easier for them.
OL,23,EPub: 15-Feb-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,158,140,200,120,0,100
