OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F157A1776888679
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G5/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCFreeview switch-off: a history
OL,4,Clesson
OL,5,
OL,6,FAnother big change in the 70s also
OL,7,Fprovoked concern for the vulnerable.
OL,9,FFor many people, the radio changes of
OL,10,F1978 simply meant retuning. Naturally
OL,11,Fthere was also a lot of promotion to
OL,12,Fhighlight the new station frequencies.
OL,13,FBut, again, for a minority this was a
OL,14,Fdifficult situation. Boy Scouts were
OL,15,Ftrained to help people retune.
OL,17,FSo, traditionally in Britain we have
OL,18,Foften gone to great lengths to help
OL,19,Fthose who are vulnerable for one reason
OL,20,For another with changes that were
OL,21,Fstraightforward for most of us.
OL,23,EPub: 15-Feb-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,158,140,200,120,0,100
