OL,3,GOPINIONCFreeview switch-off: a history
OL,4,Clesson
OL,5,
OL,6,FThat is still true.
OL,8,FI bet few would notice the end of
OL,9,Fmedium wave radio.
OL,11,FRadio Ulster and many English local
OL,12,Fstations are already off MW.
OL,14,FThe numbers listening to Radio 4 on
OL,15,Flong wave are not publicised but are
OL,16,Fthought to be tiny. If Five Live came
OL,17,Foff MW, I am sure most of its listeners
OL,18,Fwould easily find it on digital radio.
OL,23,EPub: 15-Feb-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,158,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15707
SC,0007
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F157A1776888679
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G7/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCFreeview switch-off: a history
OL,4,Clesson
OL,5,
OL,6,FYet concern for a small minority is
OL,7,Fundoubtedly the main reason why the end
OL,8,Fof AM radio has been such a slow,
OL,9,Fcareful process.
OL,11,FSo it is time for the government to
OL,12,Fmake the prerequisites for switching
OL,13,Foff public services on Freeview clear.
OL,15,FI would suggest it can be considered
OL,16,Fwhen Freeview accounts for less than
OL,17,F10pc of viewing.
OL,19,FThen a medium-term timetable along with
OL,20,Fpractical measures to help the
OL,21,Fvulnerable can be set out.
OL,23,EPub: 15-Feb-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
