OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G8/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCFreeview switch-off: a history
OL,4,Clesson
OL,5,
OL,6,FTalking about a TV switch off just now
OL,7,F` when it is a long time in the future
OL,8,F` may simply worry or scare some
OL,9,Fpeople.
OL,11,FAnd politicians should know there are
OL,12,Fsimply no votes in turning off TV.
OL,14,FDecimalisation went far more smoothly
OL,15,Fthan some feared in 1971. The trick was
OL,16,Fa gradualist approach to ensure the
OL,17,Fvast bulk of people were more than
OL,18,Fready combined with a lot of help for
OL,19,Fthose who really needed it.
OL,21,FAnyone contemplating the end of
OL,22,FFreeview should consider this lesson.
OL,23,EPub: 15-Feb-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
